      <h1 class='title'>Better Regulation Task Force</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 10 November 2004 vol 666 c21WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_21ws' title='Col. 21WS &mdash; HL Deb 10 November 2004 vol 666 c21WS' name='column_21ws' href='#column_21ws' rel='bookmark'>21WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0666P0-09664'>
        <a name='S5LV0666P0_20041110_LWS_2'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-charles-falconer' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0666P0_20041110_LWS_2' title='Link to this speech by Mr Charles Falconer' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-charles-falconer" title="Mr Charles Falconer">The Secretary of State for Constitutional Affairs and Lord Chancellor (Lord Falconer of Thoroton)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0666P0-09664">The Government have today published their response to the Better Regulation Task Force report,<span class="italic">Better Routes to Redress.</span> Copies of the government response have been placed in the Libraries of both Houses. Further copies of this response may be obtained from the Department for Constitutional Affairs and it is available on the department's website at <span class="underline">http://www.dca.gov.uk.</span> The BRTF report <span class="italic">Better Routes to Redress</span> and the government response are also available on the BRTF website at <span class="underline">http://www.brtf gov.uk.</span></p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
